Ethereum is a fast-rising cryptocurrency, second only to Bitcoin in market capitalization. In 2013, it was conceived by Vitalik Buterin, a programmer. Other founders include; Gavin Wood, Anthony Di Lorio, Charles Hoskinson and Joseph Lubin. In this article, I would be explaining a step-by-step process on how to sell your Ethereum in Nigeria, and things to consider before, during and after you take that step. Decided to dive into the crypto world and take advantage of the digital currency? You would need to select an exchange platform, create an account, deposit the cryptocurrency (in this case; Ethereum), sell it, and withdraw to your local bank account. Let’s break this down even further and shed some light on it. Step One: Pick Best Ethereum Exchange platform: This is the first step in your journey of selling ETH, and although it might not seem crucial, it is very important.
