You have selected a suitable exchange platform, next, you have to create an account. Below are the steps you’ll normally come across in an exchange platform. After you’ve done these, you would need to verify your email address. To do this, an email will be sent to the email address provided and you’ll then follow the instructions as stated in the email. Step Three – Deposit Ethereum:
Of course, to sell your Ethereum, you will need to deposit it into your wallet. To do this, you would need to generate an ETH wallet address. This wallet address is somewhat like your regular bank account number. You send it to the sender and receive your Ethereum in it after a couple of confirmations from the blockchain. An Ethereum transaction usually takes between a few seconds to ten (10) minutes to complete. For faster processing, you can choose a higher network fee. A network fee is a transaction fee incurred when you send cryptocurrency from one address to another. I guess you can say it is kind of like bank transfer charges when you transfer money between banks. This step is also quite crucial. When depositing Ethereum into your wallet, you need to double-check and verify it. Why? If you send the wrong crypto into your ETH wallet, it will be lost forever and cannot be recovered. Your Ethereum wallet allows you to receive Ethereum from anywhere in the world. Step Four- Sell Ethereum:
